  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Train Local Brigades to Fight Forest Fires in MX</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Forest fires have increased in the Sierra Gorda Biosphere Reserve due to climate change conditions and to human pressure  that leads to destroying ecosystems that are refuges to precious and endangered biodiversity. Currently across Mexico communities are unable to control forest fires because of insufficient resources. We seek to prevent fires by creating local rapid response brigades and by educating communities on fire prevention and the importance of forest conservation.</narrative>
  </description>
